                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12591965" author="aidan" created="Thu, 24 Apr 2008 09:46:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s possible the connection close tests are not correct, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-963&quot; title=&quot;SimpleACLTest.testServerPublishInvalidQueueSucces and testServerPublishUsingTransactionSuccess fail&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPID-963&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPID-963&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12592828" author="senakafdo" created="Mon, 28 Apr 2008 15:13:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch provided, reduces this from 90s to 60s. I believe that we should not retry something that is guaranteed to fail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Senaka&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12592832" author="senakafdo" created="Mon, 28 Apr 2008 15:20:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I noticed that commenting out the SUCCESS cases don&apos;t do any change to the wait. But, commenting out some FAILURE cases do reduce the wait. This points out the fact that there might be a hang in failure cases that causes this 60s (with my patch) delay.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Senaka&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12592835" author="senakafdo" created="Mon, 28 Apr 2008 15:50:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After printing out durations of each test to the stdout, it seems that,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. testUnresolvedVirtualHostFailure&lt;br/&gt;
2. testPasswordFailureConnection&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;take time. Around 20-25 seconds on each.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Senaka&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12597438" author="rhs" created="Fri, 16 May 2008 12:16:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe there is a deeper issue here  with connection negotiation. Regardless of the number of retries or the timeouts involved, these tests should pass almost instantaneously. I know one issue is that AMQConnectionDelegate_0_8.makeBrokerConnection missed some updates from the merge. The M2.x code in makeBrokerConnection tries to attain either the CONNECTION_OPEN or CONNECTION_CLOSED states, whereas the trunk code tries to only attain CONNECTION_OPEN. The former behavior seems more correct to me. I have the M2x version merged in my local checkout, however this causes a few issues that I have yet to look into.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12608696" author="aidan" created="Fri, 27 Jun 2008 08:47:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is Rafi&apos;s partial patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
